column10: Robert the Bruce King of Scots 1306-1329

Charles George Gordon R.E., C.B; Major-general; Born 28 Jaunary 1833; Fell in his country's service at Kartoum January 1885; Dedicated to his memory by Members of the Gordon Clan. I have done my best for the honour of our country. Kartoum, 14 Decr 1884.
The steel leopard stands 5m tall, weighs just over two tons, and will sit on top of a 10m high column.
A statue of Sir Robert Benholm, holding his sword with a dog at his feet.
